line_1: And carry in contusions of his scull,
And useless as a candle in a scull,
line_2: That truth itself is in her head as dull

line_1: Infuse a little Wit into the Scull,
line_2: Which never fails to make a mighty Fool;

line_1: What Phrenzy, what Delirium mars the Scull,
line_2: Which fill'd the Chests, and was it self so full?

line_1: No matter how unfurnish'd be his Scull,
line_2: Be he a Sot, incorrigibly dull:
